{"id":"0dc47d93-a778-447a-9f5c-761a68846460","title":"1498/03/27: footnote 2 (p. 133-4)","type":"main-list-block","children":[{"id":"670863b3-73ea-494b-890c-710151ba7e4c","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"There is much confusion in both the ancient and modern writers in declaring who gave the challenge, and Professor Villari, pointing out the discordance, thinks that we must conclude that the first to do so was the preacher of Santa Croce, Fra Francesco da Puglia;\u00A0Landucci makes Fra Domenico give the challenge. It appears to me, after consulting the books and documents, that there were two challenges: first the Franciscan challenged Savonarola, but without result, because the Dominican paid no heed to the provocation. Then Fra Domenico, on his side, not able to bear the attacks of the Pugliese, formulated the doctrine of his master in six conclusions, and invited the adversary to enter the fire to prove them. The latter, however, fenced, saying that his dispute was with Savonarola, and he would enter the fire with him. Both sides had gone so far that they could not recede without a scandal, to avoid which it was agreed that Fra Giuliano Rondinelli, another Franciscan, should make the test with Fra Domenico. ","standoffProperties":[{"id":"ade7f201-a3e7-461c-aede-661c159387e3","type":"page","start":0,"end":263,"value":"133","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"eb1f4d54-5c40-4ea3-ad22-b9f8a78cbef3","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":104,"end":120,"value":"8973f071-3037-44fb-83aa-41103b9717da","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"62cbeb1c-dd22-4d54-a771-629ab4d5d972","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":214,"end":221,"value":"05039e78-f1c4-435d-a888-d913e7f20371","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"35dfcbb0-f230-4c7f-b411-936f3eb17a78","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":226,"end":236,"value":"d99fbe1c-14c0-4d70-8d4b-bd3c529a28ab","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"2c303be2-337e-4b7b-98df-bd6d1af7d1e9","type":"language","start":226,"